# Generated Dart code is committed per project standard — see
# docs/standards/naming-conventions.md. *.g.dart, *.freezed.dart, and the
# files emitted by `flutter gen-l10n` under lib/l10n/generated/ are all
# intentionally tracked so contributors do not need to run code generation
# before opening the project, and so CI can detect generated-output drift.

# Bundled mermaid asset — fetched by tool/fetch_mermaid.sh, never
# committed. Pinned version + SHA-256 live in the script; CI runs
# the script before tests / builds. Keeps the repo small and forces
# a deliberate diff review when bumping mermaid.
assets/mermaid/mermaid.min.js

# Local environment
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# Secrets
*.pem
*.p12
*.p8
*.keystore

# Play Store "what's new" files — generated on the CI runner at
# release time from the annotated tag message (see release.yml).
# Never committed.
android/whatsnew/

# Personal analysis / scratch notes — this directory is a private
# working area for per-contributor checklists, one-off investigation
# logs, and other "notebook" content that should never reach the
# public history. Anything in docs/ that is part of the project
# standards or release documentation lives OUTSIDE this directory
# (e.g. docs/release-process.md, docs/standards/, docs/decisions/).
docs/analysis/

# OS
Thumbs.db
